headline: Silver Surges and Then Slumps as Precious Metals Brace for Weeks of Volatility
summary: Silver  prices hit a fresh all-time high in overnight trading before retreating sharply amid renewed volatility in precious metals markets following an historic year of gains.  Spot silver traded as high as $84 an ounce in the overnight session, a near 10% advance from last week’s close and a level that would have marked the strongest annual gain since 1951, before slumping more than 10% shortly afterward.
